cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with learning transferable features from weakly labeled data in digital pathology, which involves image analysis and classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to achieve highly competitive patch classification results, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for organizing the weakly labeled data, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia).
